Immerse yourself in a visual transformation where the precision of AI Photo converges with the inspiration of AI Art, turning average images into captivating headshots that show your personality.

reviews.text: No trial or test, charges right away without even seeing quality. Bought 60 photos, 8 are usable. Can't edit your source photos. Can't save photos to your phone, keep getting a permissions error despite full permissions granted. It's fine but where do people get off thinking this is something you can charge more than $3/ mo for? Absolutely mediocre

No trial period! There is no way I'm paying a cent without first seeing if it works. The subscription works in a way that you pay ten times more if you subscribe weekly so it seems more attractive to pay for the year. There is a reason a trial period isn't offered. Put a water mark in the trial period pics to block free downloads but at least let us know if it's any good before we buy.

Do not waste your money. I bought the package and swiftly realized they mostly just put your face on the actual examples they show you. Nothing is different. It was so bad they didn't try and grade the skin tone of my forehead into the digitized face. So it's just your actual photos, put on their example, no color adjustment or anything. Not sure if I will get any of my money back (I bought the year long subscription) but this isn't even worth a free trial (which they don't offer.) PASS

Horrible experience. Paid $7 for a trail and got one set of pictures, had to pay more money for "coins" to get more photo packages. The app froze on the second set of photos and won't let me do anything else. Ive reached out to support twice and haven't heard a word. $10 down the drain for nothing when there's better options out there for less money.
reviews.replyText: We are sorry to hear that you are having troubles with Momo. We stand behind the quality of our product and would be happy to investigate your case. Can you please contact us with your app version and device details via store@momoai.co so we may assist you further and make it up to you? We hope to speak with you soon!

reviews.text: The worst AI app on the market.. Don't waste your time. Even if you pay for the subscription it will only allow you to create six photos at a time.. then you have to wait to regenerate "coins" which takes 3 days.. OR forces you to PAY EXTRA on top of your subscription to get 6 more photos. Not worth it, photos are not natural looking at all! Still trying to understand exactly what I paid for!! Canceled within 2 hours of activating the app

Pictures only vaguely look like me. I would be embarrassed to put these anywhere except maybe show a friend how much better looking I could be if I looked like the person who the app cut and pasted part of my face onto. Not on the level I'd expect from a paid app. I purchased a week's worth and can not figure out how to cancel further payments. It's says cancel anytime, but then it doesn't give you the option to cancel. They have charged me two more times after emailing them twice to cancel.

save your money. This app Is a rip-off. when you subscribe for a week, it doesn't give you full access. it gives you 60 stars, and every pack costs between 6-60 stars. I chose three packs, and none of them generated accurate pictures. it doesn't take into consideration the body shape, and none of the pictures even looked like me. when I decided to load other pictures of me, in thhope that it gives better results. it locked me out and requested 120 stars. now I have frozen money that I can't use.

Absolutely awful.. what a total waste of money!!! A friend of mine recommended this app for professional headshots, and the headshots that were generated looked absolutely nothing like me. Not only did it not even get my eye color correct, it completely changed my hairstyle. I guess somebody must have trained the AI that professional women don't have bangs and they don't have brown eyes. When I shared the generated images with my friends, their first question was, "who is that?".

This is literally the dumbest thing I've ever spent money, I just wanted to add a neutral background to some photos for LinkedIn but this app took my face and put it on another body in the middle of a mountain range (Yes, I selected the black background AND LinkedIn prompts). Cost me $8 to sign up and I won't use it a second time, literally ever. AND the photo batches take at least 30 minutes per prompt. Absolute garbage waste of time.
reviews.replyText: We are extremely sorry for the inconvenience. We are constantly upgrading our systems so that you can have the best AI Photo Generation experience possible! Please make sure you’re using the latest version available at all times and reach out to us via store@momoai.co if you have further feedback!

reviews.text: Terrible. Once you subscribe there is absolutely no option to unsubscribe. And yes I cancelled within the time window, I did it right away in fact cuz the pics were God awful. The only button on the app, is for 'Restore Purchase' which keeps renewing! The email contact is unresponsive. I've been charged for weeks with no option to get fix it. Oh! And the pictures were the ugliest AI I've ever seen! The pics turned me into some 100 lb anorexic chic and the face was completely off.

app.AIReview:
Momo - AI Photo Generator Review

Overview

Momo – AI Photo Generator has swiftly amassed over 5.25 million installs and enjoys a robust 4.47 rating, placing it firmly within the top tier of AI-powered photo generation apps. The app’s core functionality revolves around creating professional-looking images for various purposes: business headshots, dating app profiles, social media content, and even “realistic AI photos.” The free price point is a significant draw, making it accessible to a broad audience seeking quick and easy image creation without the commitment of paid subscriptions. The app’s marketing heavily emphasizes its advanced AI technology, promising simplified image creation through AI profile training - a key selling point that underpins much of its functionality. Given the large install base and generally positive rating, this review aims to delve into whether Momo lives up to its ambitious claims and provides a genuinely useful tool for users.

Key Features

  • AI Headshot Generation: The flagship feature is undoubtedly the AI-powered headshot creation. Users input details like profession, desired style (e.g., corporate, casual, artistic), background, and even facial expressions. The app then utilizes its AI to generate multiple headshot variations based on this information.
  • Style Presets: Momo offers a selection of pre-defined style presets categorized by use case – “Business,” “Dating,” “Social Media,” and "Travel." Selecting a preset drastically streamlines the process, guiding the AI toward suitable image generation parameters.
  • Customization Options: Beyond presets, users have granular control over various aspects like lighting, color grading, background selection (including options for uploading custom backgrounds), and even adding props or accessories via an in-app library.
  • AI Profile Training: A unique feature promising to “train your AI profile” – this involves rating generated images as ‘good’ or ‘bad.’ Momo claims that repeated feedback improves the AI's ability to generate images aligned with user preferences over time. This is intended to reduce iteration and improve results.
  • Social Media Export: Direct export options for popular social media platforms (Instagram, Facebook, LinkedIn) are included, simplifying the process of sharing generated content.
  • Variety of Image Types: Beyond headshots, the app also allows for generating images based on text prompts – users can describe a scene or subject, and Momo will attempt to generate an image accordingly (though this feature seems less refined than the headshot generation).

Strengths

  • Ease of Use: Momo’s intuitive interface is one of its strongest assets. The process of creating headshots is remarkably straightforward, even for users with no prior experience in photo editing or AI tools.
  • Speed & Efficiency: Image generation within Momo is impressively fast. Headshot variations are produced in a matter of seconds, significantly reducing the time investment compared to traditional photography sessions or elaborate digital manipulations.
  • Variety of Styles: The available style presets cater to a wide range of needs and aesthetic preferences, offering users numerous options for tailoring their images.
  • Large User Base & Active Development: The app’s popularity indicates ongoing development and support, evidenced by frequent updates and feature additions. The 218,647 ratings provide valuable feedback directly from the user community.
  • Free Access: The free version provides substantial functionality, allowing users to experiment with the AI before considering a premium subscription (if offered).

Areas for Improvement

  • AI Consistency: While generally effective, the AI's output can be inconsistent. Some generated headshots are exceptionally realistic and well-suited to the specified criteria, while others fall short, exhibiting unrealistic features or awkward poses. This variability requires considerable user tweaking.
  • Limited Background Options: The background selection options could benefit from a more extensive library and potentially allow for importing custom images seamlessly. Currently, the available backgrounds feel somewhat limited and repetitive.
  • AI Profile Training Effectiveness: The “AI profile training” feature seems underdeveloped. While providing feedback is beneficial, the app doesn’t clearly demonstrate how this data is used to significantly alter the AI's generation process – users may not see a noticeable difference after repeated ratings. More transparent communication about the training algorithm would be valuable.
  • Text Prompt Generation Quality: The text-to-image feature requires substantial refinement. The generated images from textual prompts are frequently abstract or inaccurate, indicating that this function needs significant improvements before it becomes genuinely useful.
  • Lack of Advanced Editing Tools: While Momo excels at generating basic headshots, it lacks advanced photo editing tools typically found in professional photography apps (e.g., layer masking, advanced color correction).

User Experience

The user experience is overwhelmingly positive for the core headshot generation feature. The flow from selecting a style to previewing generated images is fluid and intuitive. The controls are logically arranged, making it easy for users to adjust parameters without feeling overwhelmed. However, navigating the less-used features (like text prompt generation) can feel slightly clunky due to the less polished UI elements. The app’s performance is generally smooth on a range of devices, although some reports suggest occasional lag during intensive image generation.

Value for Money

As a free app, Momo offers exceptional value. Users can experiment with its core features without any financial commitment. The potential for generating professional-looking images quickly and easily justifies the download alone. However, if users require consistently high-quality results or access to premium features (such as an expanded background library or advanced editing tools), a paid subscription would likely be warranted – the pricing structure of such a subscription needs further investigation.

Conclusion

Momo - AI Photo Generator is a genuinely impressive app that successfully demonstrates the potential of AI in simplifying image creation. Its ease of use, speed, and variety of styles make it a compelling option for anyone needing quick and accessible headshots or profile pictures. While inconsistencies in the AI's output and limitations in certain features (like text prompt generation) remain areas for improvement, Momo’s strengths significantly outweigh its weaknesses, especially given its free access. It is a strong contender within the crowded field of AI photo generators, offering a valuable tool for users seeking convenience and creativity. We rate it 4.3/5 – a solid recommendation with room for continued development.
